<template><div><p><code v-pre>Stone Env</code> is a standalone JavaScript/TypeScript library designed to provide easy access to environment
variables with built-in validation and formatting. It offers a fluent API to retrieve environment variables,
ensuring that your application's configuration is always correct and reliable.</p>
<p>With <code v-pre>Stone Env</code>, you can easily retrieve environment variables as different types, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>Strings</li>
<li>Numbers</li>
<li>Booleans</li>
<li>Arrays</li>
<li>Objects</li>
<li>JSON</li>
<li>Enums</li>
<li>Emails</li>
<li>URLs</li>
<li>Hosts</li>
</ul>
<p>With automatic validation and optional default values,
<code v-pre>Stone Env</code> ensures that your environment variables are always accurate and dependable.</p>
<p>You can access your environment variables in both backend and frontend contexts.
For frontend usage, you'll need to use a <code v-pre>Vite</code>, <code v-pre>Rollup</code> or <code v-pre>Webpack</code> plugin to handle
the replacement of environment variables at build time. We'll cover this in more detail later.</p>
</div></template>


